│ Task 121 - Document "One Search" Routing Logic (for Manav)                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ Category: Search Architecture                                                                                                                                                              │
│ Assigned To: Manav                                                                                                                                                                         │
│ Priority: P1                                                                                                                                                                               │
│ Dependencies: None                                                                                                                                                                         │
│ Description:                                                                                                                                                                               │
│ This task documents all the decisions made by Barry and Rhonda about how the "One Search" system should route users. Manav owns the search backend implementation. Robert will connect the │
│  frontend to whatever API Manav provides.                                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ The "One Search" concept: A single search input that intelligently routes to 4 different result types:                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ Type 1 - Exact POI Match (POI is in the system):                                                                                                                                           │
│ - User types a specific business name (e.g., "Creamy Cones Ice Cream"), park name ("Pittsboro Park"), service ("Barry's Website Design"), or event ("Happy Hour at Barry's Pub")           │
│ - System recognizes this matches a POI in the database                                                                                                                                     │
│ - Action: Navigate directly to that POI's detail page (e.g., /places/creamy-cones-ice-cream-pittsboro-nc)                                                                                  │
│ - This is the "easy one" - the POI exists, send them right there                                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ Type 2 - POI Not Found (searched like Type 1, but doesn't exist):                                                                                                                          │
│ - User searches for a specific place that is NOT in the database                                                                                                                           │
│ - System determines no POI matches                                                                                                                                                         │
│ - Action: Show a message below the search box: "We couldn't find [LOCATION NAME] but you can help us by adding it." with an "Add new place" button                                         │
│ - The "Add new place" button goes to the Add POI form (/addlocation/)                                                                                                                      │
│ - This encourages community contribution (important for rural communities)                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ Type 3 - Specialized Zones (broader location/area search):                                                                                                                                 │
│ - User types a town, county, shopping mall, state, or named area                                                                                                                           │
│ - Examples: "Pittsboro, North Carolina", "Chatham County", "Jordan Lake", "State of North Carolina", "Downtown Pittsboro"                                                                  │
│ - Action: Navigate to a specialized page showing:                                                                                                                                          │
│   - Explore by County/Town cards                                                                                                                                                           │
│   - "People Also Searched For" suggestions                                                                                                                                                 │
│   - Upcoming Events from that area                                                                                                                                                         │
│   - Map centered on the area with nearby POIs                                                                                                                                              │
│   - All trails in that area (if applicable, like Jordan Lake)                                                                                                                              │
│   - All businesses in that area (if applicable, like a shopping mall)                                                                                                                      │
│ - POST-MVP: This page type is not fully designed yet. For MVP, redirect to the Explore page with appropriate filters.                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ Type 4 - Keyword or Interest (mood/attribute/activity search):                                                                                                                             │
│ - User types a keyword, interest, mood, or attribute                                                                                                                                       │
│ - Examples: "pet friendly", "wheelchair accessible", "calm", "adventurous", "hiking in Boston MA", "live music", "waterfalls"                                                              │
│ - Action: Navigate to a results page showing:                                                                                                                                              │
│   - Left sidebar: Filter checkboxes by type (Businesses, Parks, Trails, Events)                                                                                                            │
│   - Map showing all matching results                                                                                                                                                       │
│   - Result cards below the map                                                                                                                                                             │
│   - All results are places matching that keyword/attribute                                                                                                                                 │
│ - This is where the hybrid AI search shines - semantic search understands "adventurous" or moods                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ How to determine which type: The backend search API needs to classify the query:                                                                                                           │
│ 1. If the query exactly or closely matches a POI name → Type 1                                                                                                                             │
│ 2. If the query looks like a specific place name but has no match → Type 2                                                                                                                 │
│ 3. If the query matches a known location/area/zone → Type 3                                                                                                                                │
│ 4. Otherwise → Type 4                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ Current search state: The existing SearchBar.jsx uses /api/pois/hybrid-search?q={query}&limit=50 which returns POI results. It doesn't classify query type. This classification logic      │
│ needs to be added, either frontend-side (by analyzing results) or backend-side (preferred).                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ ---                                                                                                                                                                                        │
